Irish businessman Eddie Jordan has been involved in motorsport since the early ‘70’s. In 1991 he founded his Formula 1 team, Jordan Grand Prix. He would like to see the South African Grand Prix return. eNCA’s Justin Ford reports. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Last year’s battle between Lewis Hamilton and Max Verstappen for the Formula 1 championship seems to have re-ignited motorsport’s flagship event. Fans are looking forward to the start of the new season in two months’ time, although there's uncertainty surrounding Hamilton’s return. The seven-time champion also wants to see the South African Grand Prix make a comeback after 30 years. READ: Cape Town Grand Prix hopes to host the F1 It’s a sentiment shared by former team owner Eddie Jordan. Jordan has made Cape Town his home, and naturally, he would like to see the South African Grand Prix return. * eNCA’s Justin Ford reports.